Re: auto backing up of wallet.dat

Bitcointalk

2010-08-27 02:54:07 UTC - [11]Original Post

   I doubt thereʼs an mmap(2) on Windows.  Iʼd rather call an existing
   file copy function than make and test my own.
   [12]Quote from: nelisky on August 27, 2010, 01:21:09 AM
   But if you are already using features from boost::filesystem you can
   use copy_file from that. I just think that, if not already required for
   something else, itʼs a tad overkill.
   Thanks.  I thought it would be in there somewhere.
   We already use boost::filesystem in a dozen places.  Itʼs not a new
   added dependency.  It gives us a lot of portable stuff that we would
   otherwise have to have a #ifdef for each OS and test everywhere.
